By Kamarudeen Ogundele Abuja A former member of the House of Representatives and Chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Sunday Karimi, on Thursday backed President Muhammadu Buhari for the removal of subsidy on petroleum. He blamed previous governments of former presidents Olusegun Obasanjo and Goodluck Jonathan for wasting tax payers money on the subsidy regime, which he noted, was a conduit for fraud. In a statement in Abuja on Thursday, Karimi who twice represented Yagba Federal Constituency of Kogi State on the platform of Peoples Democratic Party, urged Nigerians irrespective of their political or religious beliefs to support the move According to him, the deregulation of the downstream sector would help to save money for the country. He also urged the president to use the gains to improve the infrastructure and welfare of Nigerians. Karimi said, “One of the major draining pipes and sources of wastage and corruption in Government finances is the high subsidy being paid by government for the pump prices of petrol for ages, the effect of the subsidy doesn’t reflect positively on common man on the street. “President Buhari with his long term experience in the industry took a right decision. Previous administrations since 1999 demonstrated lack of political will to safe the nation from this unnecessary wastage under the guise of subsidy.” 